                         Thunderstorm with anvil...

                             [rainbow-bar2.gif]

    ... as seen from the Black Hills in July, 1979. The anvil forms when
    the buoyant air in a cumulonimbus cloud reaches a stable layer (warm
    stratospheric air). This acts like a mechanical lid forcing the cloud
                             material sideways.

          For more weather photographs, see Steve Albers's homepage
